description:
In the magical land of Bablashca, card-shaped relics are discovered that are part of the ancient Culdcept, a book that created the universe. Whoever collects all the cards will have the power of gods, but only special people, called Cepters, can control the cards, and thus, control the universe. When the mysterious Black Ceptors begin destroying city after city in search of the precious cards, the fate of Bablashca rests in an apprentice Cepter named Najaran, who sets out on an improbable journey to conquer the Black Cepters before they discover the hidden relics.

  • Round 1: Najaran, A Novice Cepter - The Beginning of Her Adventure
  • Round 2: The Cepters' Battle Tournament
  • Round 3: Code of the Cepters
  • Round 4: Dragon-Eyed Zeneth Storms In
  • Round 5: Tempest
  • Round 6: The Final Battle!

  • Round 8: The Old Hero
  • Round 9: The Last Card
  • Round 10: Black Banquet (Part One)
  • Round 11: Black Banquet (Part Two)
  • Etra Rounds: The Creature Books

description:
In the "War of Gods," Culdra was forced to scatter the power of the Culdcept, the book of creation, into numerous card-like relics. Cepters are among a special group of people who can control the cards, and thus, control the universe... Najaran is an apprentice Cepter with an appetite for adventure ... and a passion to eat! She must protect the world from the Black Cepters who will stop at nothing to get their hands on the ancient relics. However Najaran is confronted with her toughest mission yet...fasting!

description:
While Najaran and her companions enjoy lunch in a quiet forest, the silence is soon broken by the thundering stampede of frantic forest critters and the twisted visage of a full-grown Woodfolk comes crashing into view. Is this normally peaceful creature under the spell of the rumored 'Black Cepters'...or is she simply barking up the wrong tree?

description:
Najaran and her friends finally clear all the gates, but their adventure doesn't end there. They encounter Dark Master, who has been unsealed after being confined for centuries in Old-Willow. After a triumphant battle with Dark Master, Najaran is given a special card called "Hope"...but what power does that special card wield? Is it a missing piece to finding Black Cepter's whereabouts?

The Cepters' Guild loses one of its members! The Guild members continue to fight amongst one another while the Dark Ceptors prevail in taking over the world. Najaran encounters the Guild Master who is one of the 4 Elemental Kings. The Guild must discover which Elemental King holds the card to win against the Dark Ceptors.

Alex Ross illustrates a vibrant, hallucinatory tour of modern America as seen through the eyes of a homeless man who may be the living spirit of America in this new hardcover edition of a Vertigo classic. With dynamic painted art by Alex Ross, UNCLE SAM is the story of a star-spangled vagrant clad in red, white and blue, guided by the voices in his head and his own fractured memories. Absorbed by history-traveling visions of America's dark past, Uncle Sam struggles to piece together the scattered clues of his own experiences in this deep and thoughtful look at America's checkered past.
name: HC

description:
In this latest SCALPED volume, collecting issues #25-29 of the acclaimed series, we see the landscape of the Prairie Rose reservation and casino through the eyes of a newcomer — a card shark and con man — whose presence could spell doom for one of our main characters.

Back Blurb

Five's a crowd

Dash Bad Horse is a drug-addled soldier in the crime family of Chief Red Crow -but he's also the undercover FBI agent assigned to bring Red Crow down.

Baylis Earl Nitz is Bad Horse's FBI supervisor - but he's also on a bloody quest for vengeance against Red Crow that's much more personal than business.

Britt "Diesel" Fillenworth is a sociopathic thug in jail for multiple murders - but he's also Nitz's undercover ace in the hole.

Catcher is a burned-out alcoholic mystic - but he's also a former radical with secrets darker than anyone could imagine.

And a mystery man with a thousand faces has come to Red Crow's reservation to swindle its casino - but he also has a secret link to Dash that could destroy both halves of Bad Horse's double life.

Now a high-stakes heist has this powder keg of explosive personalities set to blow. Before it's all over, blood will be spilled, secrets will be revealed, and Dash's life will never be the same...

Writer Jason Aaron (THE OTHER SIDE, Wolverine) and artists R.M. Guera, Davide Furno and Francesco Francavilla present a pivotal volume in this Eisner Award nominated crime saga.

description:
Razor battles the demented Rush as she straps a bomb to a cop, who was trying to empty a refuge center that she planned to bomb, and is taken aback when Rsh knows her real name. Nicole!  The bomb explodes killing the cop and the fight moves to the next building as Rush makes her escape. Something Rush says reminds razor of her sister Stryke.
 
Meanwhile in Spain Knyfe/Kat meets Nicoles daughter Alexis and tries to get her away with her to be like her mother. but Alexis hits her and tells her that she wont be like her mother. 
 
Razor battles Rush who tells her she is wired to explode herself and shes hidden a bomb at the clinic and will take out everything she loves. Razor is enraged that she will hurt those she loves and in a flurry shreds the clothes and equipment off Rush and the bomb explodes far enough away for the two of them escape.  
 
At Nicole's clinic things seem all clean and the bomb is a fake that comes to life when Rush's body-bomb blows. Its a faxing unit and produces an image of Rush and Razor as purifiers cleaning up the city.
name: Everybody Hurts

description:
In his dreams Greg has flashbacks to his tryst with Stryke and the shame it brings him haunts his worklife and relationships. When he goes to Nicole's for a meal Jeanna gets spooked with a cop in the house and panics. 
 
Nicole seems just a obsessed by Stryke's influence on her life she her sister in her reflection and in a jumble of emotions she goes and takes a shower. Greg seeing her naked body scarred and muscled in the shower again can only compare it to Stryke's and his fantasies with Nicole mingle with thoughts of Stryke.
name: Everybody Hurts

description:
Nicole wakes from a night with Greg and is shocked that she slept with him.. just as much as he is shocked he slept with her. Nicole see's how brutal her love making is when Razor takes over and Greg is covered in marks and bites. Her metal state is fragile and she is attacked by a phantom Razor and escapes the building as Razor.  
 
She sees a little girl and chases after her as Poizon sends her a warning not to follow. She ignores it and sees the little girl looks like Stryke and she follows the little girl as she scales a building.  Atop the building an adult  Stryke is kissing Greg and they fight, Greg shots at Razor after she slashes Strykes throat out. Razor takes him down with a blade to the chest. the angel in black takes her hand and flies over the city and dops her from high above the streets.  
 
Nicole wakes to find Greg dressing and she leaps on him and smashes his head on the floor over and over... until she realizes this is no long a dream.
name: Everybody Hurts

description:
Razor stalks the city and comes across a building on fire. A woman cries for her granddaughter trapped in the building. razor leaps into action and finds a man in the building alive and she gets him out first and goes back in for the girl. She finds her too late and seconds later the building comes down. Razor survives but hears the man is a convicted arsonist. He claims innocence to the police but his attitude after leads her to think he might be the culprit after all.  
 
Razor follows him and from a rooftop hears him on a phone telling someone that the stuff he was given wasn't right and the fire started too quickly for him. Razor stalks him and finds him with a bomb. She pins him down and he confesses the man behind the fire was Victor Hammon. The Police are on hand to hear the confession and take him away promising he will go down for the crime. 
 
Razor takes the bomb he was to pick up and takes it to Hammon's mansion where the drug lord lives. She takes out his men and cuffs him to the bed with the bomb on count down. The explosion takes out the mansion. 
 
In prison the arsonist brags his crimes to his huge room mate, prisoner 666, whose sister was a victim of one of the fires.
